Feedback: Every row and every column has a circle, diamond and a square in it. In addition, each row and column has one cell with one, two and three concentric shapes. Therefore, the missing cell needs to have three concentric shapes and be a diamond. Press any key to continue.

The elements of row 2 are subtracted from the elements of row 1 to produce row 3. The same rule is applied to the columns, where the elements in column 2 are subtracted from the elements in column 1 to produce column 3. Press any key to continue.
The cross pieces are moving down towards the center of the object. The number of objects also increases going down the rows. Press any key to continue.

The elements of row 1 are added to row 2 to produce row 3. The same rule is applied to the columns, where the elements in column 1 are added to the elements in column 1 to produce column 2. In addition, the dots go to the corners of the outside square and the strips go inside the inside square, but remain outside the central circle. Therefore, two rules are used. Press any key to continue.

Going across the columns, the bottom square is removed from each element in column 1 to produce column 2.  And again, the bottom square is removed from each element in column 2 to produce column 3. And additional rule is applied going down the rows that produces the same effect. Each element in row one contains a single line, each element in row 2 contains two lines, each element in row 3 contains three lines. Press any key to continue.
